Section 4: Coding Tasks

Example 4.1

User

Write a Python quicksort implementation.
AI Response
def quicksort(arr):
if len(arr) <= 1: return arr
p = arr[len(arr)//2]
return quicksort([x for x in arr if x < p]) + \
[x for x in arr if x == p] + \
quicksort([x for x in arr if x > p])

Example 4.2

User

Write a Python function to count vowels in a string.
AI Response
def count_vowels(s):
return sum(1 for c in s.lower() if c in "aeiou")

print(count_vowels("Hello World")) # 3

Example 4.3

User

Write a Python function to group dicts by a key.
AI Response
from collections import defaultdict

def group_by(items, key):
g = defaultdict(list)
for item in items: g[item[key]].append(item)
return dict(g)

